<br>
After starting EQ a year ago with my wizard and only fiddling with other classes once in a while on other servers when I get bored of quadding (playing almost all classes up to around 10 - 15th level, just to get a taste), I've recently begun to get serious on another server with a warrior.  Unfortunately, after playing a caster exclusively for so long, I've picked up habits and tendencies and bias about certain things that make adjusting to a warrior difficult, even moreso I think than if I had never played any other class at all.  So, I have a couple of question that I'd very much appreciate help with:<br>
<br>
1.  From what I've overheard (or over-read, actually) in the last year, damage/delay is NOT the end all-be all factor in determining the value of a weapon.  Because of dual wield, rules on damage bonuses, aggro control, procs, and other factors, a better damage/delay isn't always what is best.  What I've managed to learn, whether right or wrong (if it's wrong or right but with a significant exception I should know about, let me know), is that to hold agro, you want faster weapons over slower weapons with equal DPS, and a agro-causing proc is good.  I've also heard for pure DPS without regard to agro, you want a fast weapon in the main slot and a high damage weapon in your offhand (which kinda seems suspect to me because of damage bonuses only being applied to the main hand AND going up as delay goes up and the offhand weapon not firing sometimes because of dual wield and double attack skills missing, but I'm of course minimally educated about it).  I'd really like to hear thoughts on this and maybe have someone clarify what I want if I wanna hold agro and what I want if I want to maximize my damage output should I not be MA, and maybe something else I might need to know that I haven't thought about that's related to this subject.<br>
<br>
2.  Other than 1hs and 2hs weapons being more plentiful and easier to run into pretty much from newbieland to the higherst tier PoP zones than 1hb and 2hb weapons, is there any reason alot of people tend to focus on the former and let the latter catch up slowly or not at all?  I understand the stats and effect of damage/delay, etc are identical, and there is no damage type differences in EQ (like piercing, crushing, slashing, etc.), so I can't really think of anything.<br>
<br>
3.  I haven't experienced this yet, and being only up to level 29, I won't for a while still, but what do I need to know about high-level mobs and thier abilities like summon (which I DO know about because of my wizard...goddamn worst mob ability ever!!!), rampage, enrage, etc.  I've heard raid leaders tell people in briefing to stop attacking from the front in certain situations, and to stop attacking altogether, and such, and would really like to maybe get at least a brief explanation of those things.<br>
<br>
I think that's about all I'm concerned about right now.  I'm sure there'll be more that comes up, but I'll worry about that then.  Thanks in advance to anyone who posts anything even remotely useful.<br>
<br>
