<br>
Here's how rampage works, roughly.<br>
<br>
First, you know about the hate list.  Whoever has pissed off the mob the most is on top of the hate list, and the mob targets that person... other people are on the list too, just not on top.  The hate list is fluid... you are added whenever you piss the mob off, and then your position changes based on what you do.<br>
<br>
Rampage is totally different.  It is a static list, unlike hate.  It's set right before the mob rampages for the first time, and at that time it's a carbon copy of the hate list.  It doesn't change after that, though.  Mobs will always rampage the top person on the Rampage list who is 1) not on top of the hate list and 2) in range (note that rampage range is not the same as normal attack range... sometimes it's very very large).  <br>
<br>
After the list is set, it can be added to, but not subtracted from, and positions do not change.<br>
<br>
Note that Mem Blur and sometimes fiegn death can clear the Rampage list.<br>
<br>
Also note that if you die and come back, you're still on the list in your old position, usually.  However, if you die, and then someone new agros the mob before you are rezzed, it is possible for that person to be put in your old spot (thus kicking you off the list).  Non tanks should be careful to avoid hitting the mob right after a rampage tank goes down for this reason... if you weren't already on the rampage list, you'll be put in the ramage tank spot.<br>
<br>
Rampage tanking, then, is simple.  Just get a tank class to be second in agro at the point when the rampage list is set, and you're good to go.  <br>
<br>
Note that dexterity debuffs limit rampage and flurry, since they are treated as procs.  Thus, cripple and dex poisons are quite useful against heavy rampagers.<br>
<br>
And now I'm sleepy, so that's all on the Rampage ability for tonight!<br>
