<br>
Nez:  Sneak speed increases from level 50 to 60, until at 60 you run at normal pace.  You always jump, sidestep, back up, and swim at the same crawl speed, though.  However, with Runspeed AAs I was going above normal run speed at 55, just from having run 3.<br>
<br>
Strength somewhat indirectly affects attack rating, which affects average hit.  Note that max damage doesn't change... that's always a factor of your level and the weapon damage stat.  However, higher attack rating causes you to hit for your max more often... lower attack rating causes you to hit for minimum damage.  Note that the actual comparison is your attack rating against the mob's &quot;mitigation&quot; AC.  The higher the mobs mitigation AC, the more attack rating you need to hit it for decent damage.  Luclin boss mobs are notorious for having way too much of the stuff.  The other kind is avoidance AC, by the way... the number you see on your screen is a composite of the two.  In beta you could see both, but players thought it was too confusing so they compounded to two numbers into one.  Avoidance AC affects how often you get hit, and is compared against the attackers level and weapon skill.  <br>
<br>
With all that said, even though one point of strength gives one point of attack rating, not all attack rating is the same.  You're better off getting 10 points of raw attack rating (from an aura of battle item like the belt of the great turtle, for example) than 50 points of strength, as far as damage output goes.  Kinda wacky.  This is why rogues love ranger buffs.<br>
<br>
The only differences between mainhand and off hand are that the main hand weapon isn't affected by duel weild skill (obviously) and that the main hand gets damage bonus.  The reason fast weapons are better main hand is that you get your damage bonus added to every hit... so if you use a delay 20 weapon instead of a delay 40 weapon, you hit twice as much and thus get twice as much out of your damage bonus.  That's why the lamentation is so much better than the Centi Longsword main hand at high level.  At lower levels (such as 28, where you get your first point of damage bonus... it goes up once every three levels) this won't matter so much... it's only 1 damage per hit.  But at high levels, getting an extra  11 damage per hit at level 58 matters quite a bit.  With that said the lammy is overrated, and overpriced on this server.<br>
<br>
But what Bjond said is accurate.  At low levels, max your skills.  Get a Wurmslayer, by the way... at your level the loss of damage bonus isn't so bad, and last I checked it was pretty cheap.  Questing for it is even cheaper.  I calculated it out... Wurmslayer outdamages a Lamentation until level 55 I think it was.  <br>
